def merge_sort(a):
  n = len(a)
  if n <= 1:
    return

  mid = n // 2
  g1 = a[:mid]
  g2 = a[mid:]
  merge_sort(g1)
  merge_sort(g2)

  ia, i1, i2 = 0, 0, 0
  while i1 < len(g1) and i2 < len(g2):
    if g1[i1] < g2[i2]:
      a[ia] = g1[i1]
      ia += 1
      i1 += 1
    else:
      a[ia] = g2[i2]
      ia += 1
      i2 += 1

  while i1 < len(g1):
    a[ia] = g1[i1]
    ia += 1
    i1 += 1
  while i2 < len(g2):
    a[ia] = g2[i2]
    ia += 1
    i2 += 1
